  "texts": [
    "Employing the protocol defined in Supplementary Section 6 we modified a total of 3,930 structures, which corresponds roughly to 20% of the original database that needed substantial refinement (Fig. 2).",
    "Of these, 3,905 cases involve changes in protonation states, while changes in heteroatoms involve 97 ligands.",
    "These are predominantly the addition of model functional groups to emulate covalent binding with the protein (20) or the addition of missing hydroxyl groups to boronic acids.",
    "N atoms corresponds to total changes in the atom count when compared with the source database.",
    "In most cases atoms were removed N rem atoms); in only 27% of cases was the number of atoms increased, N add atoms."
  ],
